---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy | Atriopelago"
  description="How Atriopelago processes personal data: contact form, analytics and your GDPR rights."
  lang="en"
  altPath="/polityka-prywatnosci"
>
  <main id="main" tabindex="-1" class="section container legal">
    <span class="eyebrow">Document</span>
    <h1 class="display">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">Last updated: 3 June 2026.</p>

    <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
    <p>
      The controller of your personal data is Atriopelago. For any data-protection
      matter, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:officepelago@gmail.com">officepelago@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact form:</strong> name, email address, property name and your
        message, provided voluntarily so we can get back to you.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics (Umami):</strong> anonymous, aggregated visit statistics
        (visits, entry page, country, device type). Umami uses no cookies and collects
        no data that identifies you.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Purposes and legal basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Handling your enquiry — art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (steps toward a contract) and
        art. 6(1)(f) (our legitimate interest in responding to contact).
      </li>
      <li>
        Statistics and improving the site — art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest),
        on anonymous data.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      This site uses no tracking or marketing cookies. Our analytics tool Umami works
      without cookies, so we display no cookie-consent banner. If we add advertising
      tools in the future (e.g. the Meta pixel), we will ask for your consent first.
    </p>

    <h2>5. How long we keep data</h2>
    <p>
      Form data is kept for as long as needed to handle your enquiry, and then for the
      limitation period of any potential claims. Analytics data is anonymous and aggregated.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Recipients</h2>
    <p>
      We use trusted providers who process data on our behalf: site hosting (Netlify)
      and analytics (Umami). We do not sell your data.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to: access your data, rectify it, erase it, restrict processing,
      data portability, object to processing, and lodge a complaint with the relevant
      supervisory authority (in Poland, the President of the Personal Data Protection
      Office, PUODO). To exercise these rights, email
      <a href="mailto:officepelago@gmail.com">officepelago@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy. The current version is always on this page, with the
      date of last update shown at the top.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top:32px;">
      <a href="/en" class="btn btn-primary">Back to homepage</a>
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-top: 120px;
    padding-bottom: 96px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 40px 0 12px;
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal li {
    color: var(--mist);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .legal strong {
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--sand);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
